Reply or Reply all
Link preview

When you open a message that contains a hyperlink or add a link to a message, Outlook inserts a preview of the website. If you don't want to see previews, clear the check box below. Learn more

Undo send

You can cancel an email message after you've selected Send. To cancel, select the Undo button that appears at the bottom of your screen.

Joyful animations

Outlook automatically shows a celebratory burst of colorful shapes in the reading pane when you open a message that includes words like Happy Birthday and Congratulations. To turn off these animations, clear the check box below.

Quick suggestions

As you type a message, Outlook can highlight keywords in the text and suggest helpful information, like restaurants near you, flight information, or schedules for your favorite sports teams. When you click a keyword, suggestions appear that you can insert in your message.

Suggested replies

When you open a message, Outlook might suggest replies below the message. If you select a reply, you can edit the reply before sending it. 

Text predictions

Outlook can suggest words and phrases as you compose messages. When Outlook offers a suggestion, press Tab or the right arrow key to accept it.
